\begin_inset Formula $n\times m$
\end_inset

 matrix over 
\begin_inset Formula $\mathbb{R}$
\end_inset

.
 In this case, the map 
\begin_inset Formula $f\colon U\to W$
\end_inset

 has the form
\begin_inset Formula 
\begin{eqnarray*}
f\colon U & \longrightarrow & W\\
u=(u_{1},\dots,u_{m})^{\top} & \mapsto & (f_{1}(u),\dots,f_{n}(u))^{\top}=f(u),
\end{eqnarray*}

\end_inset

